Sentencas: In this study, the microstructural and electrochemical properties of linear type nanofibers obtained by adding SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+d (SBSCO) layered perovskite oxide were investigated for use as cathode materials in a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of electrospinning-fabricated layered perovskite used in cathode materials for a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Linear type SBSCO fiber and Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-d coated SBSCO-fiber were fabricated using the electrospinning process.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of electrospinning-fabricated layered perovskite used in cathode materials for a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It was confirmed that the area specific resistance (0.75 Omega cm(2)) of the obtained SBSCO-fiber cathode was much lower than that (1.25 Omega cm(2)) of a powder-type SBSCO cathode at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of electrospinning-fabricated layered perovskite used in cathode materials for a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The result shows that the SBSCO fiber cathode exhibits lower polarization resistance in low temperature ranges than the powder SBSCO cathode materials do.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of electrospinning-fabricated layered perovskite used in cathode materials for a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A significantly lower activation energy (0.76 eV) was observed in fiber SBSCO cathode than in the nanostructured La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-d ones which were used as control at 1.53 eV.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of electrospinning-fabricated layered perovskite used in cathode materials for a low temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell
